				<td colspan="2"><span>Ill disagree with tenamin on one point although the degree of difficulty will depend upon the gear you have.
<br />

<br />
The Aria of Asceticsim would be a challange for a mid-low 40s group.  While the bard can be solo'ed by swarming in the 50s resists would kill you in the mid 40s.  Dulak in general would be a good place to go especally if you fought your way to the bar and held it.
<br />

<br />
For other suggestions:  The ice forge shackles is a fun but somewhat long quest.  Likewise doing the entrance to kael (either side) would be good and has an advantage that you can go as deep as you can handle.
<br />

<br />
Kedge is a great zone even if you dont want to try phini but get a good map.  Just going through kedge will feel like a raid.
<br />

<br />

<br />

