				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Quests/Hunts for the 40s bards<a name="21882"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 17 04 12:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I Got a Mask of Decption just 2 days ago.  I was lvl 37.  Freaking CAKE to get down here.  Bards have the Tools to accomplish this with a bit of challenge, but worth trying.
<br />

<br />
I am well geared so maybe someone with less wouldn't be too advisable.
<br />

<br />
Items needed:
<br />
IVU potions.
<br />
1 Gate potion
<br />
Solid gear
<br />
Huge Cahones
<br />

<br />
Buy 10 dose IVU (invis undead) potions.  This will get you to the batroom if you follow the guide on this site.  I tried the run past immediately but always had 2 Bats agro. Charm one, let em fight it out (This part was scary as h*ll), Kill the one that survived.
<br />

<br />
Once past that point IVU back up. and follow the guide all the way to Assassin room.  If not camped then you have a small challenge.  When I was there Assassin saw me through IVU, or regular Camo.  All 3 mobs agroed, Got smished first try.  CR back with the same strategy.  Got there, pulled corpse into the corridor to the left right next to the ladder to Assassin room.  Looted up.  IVU then sat watching the area for a bit, there is one roamer that walks past this area so time it right and you can do it.  
<br />

<br />
Once I got timing figured out I managed to get a mob targeted by clicking along the area atop the ladder (guess what it was the assassin).  Lulled him, quickly IVUed up the ladder target another mob, Lull it, then pull the other mob.  By this time Lull had worn off on the Assassin.  YUCK!!!  I got two pull.  Quickly charmed the Mob I pulled and sicked him on the Assassin.  They fought a bit, charm wore off a couple times, Got him re-charmed and let em go at it again.  Roamer came around, Mezz him.  Assassin killed my pet eventually, but by this time the Assassin was at 23% life.  He turns at 20% so it didn't take long.  Slow/Snare song, and hacked him down the rest of the way.  Keeping other mob Mezzed as it wears off.
<br />

<br />
I ended up looting the mask at 10% life with 1 mezzed mob.  I kept him in the safe corner at the left of the ladder to Assassin room while twisting heal and Mezz songs.  Got myself to 100%.  Charmed the mezzed mob, sicked him on a Mob in another room, ran back to my safe spot, clicked Gate potion back to PoK with my mask in my bag..
<br />

<br />
And I had a blast too boot.  I love a good personal challenge.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
