				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Quests/Hunts for the 40s bards<a name="22005"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 17 04 7:12 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The Eye of the Owlbear Mother, a FT1 range item that is an uncommon drop from Skriat Chakku, who spawns in the Vah Shir fort after the owlbears win the Hollowshade War (with a little help from you!).  
<br />

<br />
A decent group of mid-40s should be able to do this, though depending on your levels it can be quite a challenge, especially if you have a less-than-full group.  You'll probably want/have to do it multiple times, so the challenge can also be to see how you can improve your performance, succeed with fewer people, etc.  <i>Molto Espressivo</i>, the all-bard guild on Firiona Vie, does it fairly often in groups of 3 to 6 bards, and one of our ex-members has soloed it at 52.  There are a lot of good guides on the war floating around, so give it a try.
<br />

<br />
One thing that I haven't seen in any guide to the Hollowshade war is that the sonic wolf defenders (you'll know what that means if you check out a guide) seem weaker if you can have them in the owlbear caves to the north, rather than their home cave in the east.  This may help a little if you are having trouble or find yourself underpowered.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
