			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Quests/Hunts for the 40s bards<a name="22684"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 20 04 10:18 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have one for you.  Not too easily accomplished, but I did it solo last night at lvl 39.
<br />

<br />
Gnoll Slayer.  (Spoiler warning)
<br />

<br />
Starts in Qeynos Hills.
<br />

<br />
Go to the Merchant shack on the path and Hail Marton Sayer.  I don't have exact text, but you can read that as you go.  Basically his child is in danger blaah blaah.
<br />

<br />
Head on over to Blackburrow, once inside run down to the spike room and sit down there looking toward the door down in the spike pit.  This shouldn't take long at all.
<br />

<br />
Lord Elgnub will eventually spawn.  Kill him  and loot the Baby Joseph Sayer.  This part will be cake easy.
<br />

<br />
Now head back to the shack and give Marton his child back he will repay you with a Gnoll Slayer (crappy version) and tell you to be aware of it's true potential.
<br />

<br />
Now to finish it up you'll have to run over to South Karana and zone into Infected Paw.  Once inside you'll want to sing the invis song run back to the double doors go through them, then another door straight ahead.  You'll come to a short bridge, walk to the middle of the bridge and jump off of the right side.  
<br />

<br />
You should from there be able to see a door just ahead and to the left.  Go through that door and there will be a single Gnoll standing by a campfire.  9 times outa 10 it'll be a One Eyed Gnoll.  You'll want to kill him and loot a Gnolls Eye.  If it isn't the One Eye, kill the Placeholder.  One Eye is a very common spawn so this shouldn't take long, he is Warrior type so no worries about casting.  He was a bit of a tough fight straight Melee for me at lvl 39.  The battle ended with me at 30% life, and I mezzed him and healed up about halfway through the fight.  FYI he heals up as fast as you do with your song.  This doesn't help much.
<br />

<br />
Now you'll want to go back out the door you came in, take a left and follow the trail around (but not up) some steps.  As long as you go through no doors or up no steps you'll run right into a room with two gnolls in it.  First Spawn on the left is a Leth Mal Scribe (spelling may be off) or it's placeholder.  The Scribe is an Enchanter class mob, can be a major pain in the butt, but shouldn't pose too much of a threat.  The scribe is the guy you are looking for.  You'll wanna kill him and loot a Journal (dunno exact name of item.)  Once again, same as the One Eye, it is a VERY common spawn so you shouldn't have to clear more than one or two placeholders.  The other will be a standard Paw mob.
<br />

<br />
I stayed invised and healed back up from the One Eye fight, and watched for roamers and such.  One roamer came by for a couple seconds and didn't see him again for quite a while.
<br />

<br />
Here is how the Battle happened:
<br />

<br />
I started off Charming the second mob and sicking him on the Scribe.  Well I dunno about resists or what, but charm never stuck for more than a couple seconds, so I just kept him mezzed.
<br />

<br />
I Twisted nothing more than my standard melee lineup.  Slow, Heal, Haste songs.  And straight up meleed.  Scribe landed a couple DoTs, instill, Slow, and Mezzed me 3 times.  But once again as long as you keep your Snare/Slow song on him his melee is totally gimp so you'll not take much damage at all.  Just keep fighting.  It'll take a few minutes, and a few mezzes on the extra mob, but you should be able to take him out.  And loot the Journal (again exact name escapes me).
<br />

<br />
Once you have your crappy Gnoll Slayer, Your Gnoll Eye, and your Journal, head back to Marton Sayer and give them all back to him.  He'll return to you a Full Version of the Gnoll Slayer.  While it looks like a crappy weapon (it is by todays standards) take a closer look.  You now have a right clicky of the lvl 34 shaman pet that you can use as early as lvl 34.  Don't have to worry about this one breaking charm, and it is quite fun to play round with.  I redo this quest with my Ranger every time I use one up.
<br />

<br />
Here are the stats:
<br />

<br />
Gnoll Slayer
<br />

<br />
Primary/Secondary
<br />
No Drop
<br />
Skill: 1HS Attack Delay:40
<br />
DMG: 15
<br />
Bane Damage: Gnoll + 10
<br />
Charges: 2
<br />
Effect: Companion Spirit (casting time: Instant)
<br />
Save Disease +25
<br />
Classes: War, Pal, Rng, Shd, Rog, Brd
<br />
Race: All
<br />
Slot 1: Type 4.
<br />

<br />
Yes, your Warrior, Paladin, Ranger, and Rogue can have a pet.
<br />

<br />
This looks like a crappy weapon.  But just for grins head back into Paw, equip a Wurmy in primary 40dly, 25dmg.  And this in secondary 40dly, 25dmg (against gnolls).  And smile as you watch them gnolls fall to you insanely fast.  Fun weapon.
<br />

<br />
This is too easy if you grab up a couple Warriors of Rogues to do the quest with you.  And they'll jump at the chance to have a pet.
<br />

<br />

<br />
 
<br />
</span></td>
